<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora leucostoma" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="leucostoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora leucostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common species causing canker disease on 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
in China (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1136/bmj.1.5333.808" author="Teng, SC" journalOrPublisher="Australasian Plant Pathology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B43" refString="Teng, SC, 1963. Fungi of China. Science Press, 1-808. https://doi.org/10.1136/bmj.1.5333.808" title="Fungi of China. Science Press, 1 - 808." url="https://doi.org/10.1136/bmj.1.5333.808" year="1963">Teng 1963</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tai, FL" journalOrPublisher="Australasian Plant Pathology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B42" refString="Tai, FL, 1979. Sylloge fungorum sinicorum. Science Press, 1-1527." title="Sylloge fungorum sinicorum. Science Press, 1 - 1527." year="1979">Tai 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, JC" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B48" refString="Wei, JC, 1979. Identification of Fungus Handbook. Science Press, 1-780." title="Identification of Fungus Handbook. Science Press, 1 - 780." year="1979">Wei 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 45" refId="B8" refString="Fan, XL, Bezerra, JDP, Tian, CM, Crous, PW, 2020. Cytospora (Diaporthales) in China. Persoonia 45: 1 - 45, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" title="Cytospora (Diaporthales) in China." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" volume="45" year="2020">Fan et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, fresh specimens were collected from diseased branches of the Chinese chestnut for the first time and identified as 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora leucostoma" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="leucostoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora leucostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on strictly matched asexual morph (4-5.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
from 
<taxonomicName class="Thecofilosea" family="Castanellidae" genus="Castanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Castanea mollissima" order="Phaeocalpida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mollissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Castanea mollissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this study vs. 4.5-5.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
from multiple specimens in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 45" refId="B8" refString="Fan, XL, Bezerra, JDP, Tian, CM, Crous, PW, 2020. Cytospora (Diaporthales) in China. Persoonia 45: 1 - 45, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" title="Cytospora (Diaporthales) in China." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" volume="45" year="2020">Fan et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
) and phylogenic analysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Maximum parsimony phylogram of Cytospora obtained from the combined matrix of ITS, LSU, ACT and RPB 2 genes. Bootstrap value ≥ 50 % for MP and ML analyses are presented at the first and second position. Scale bar = 200 nucleotide substitutions. The strains in the current study are in blue and ex-strains are marked with *." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.62.47425.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/371653" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
